{"id":"xpoinittest-69a413","type":"CREATE","payload":{"title":"Browser COLORBLOXX Game","description":"## Overview\n\nA browser-based COLORBLOXX game built with React.\n\n## Key Requirements\n\n- **Grid:** Standard 10-wide x 20-tall playfield\n- **Pieces:** Four tetrominoes — Square (2x2), Bar (4x1), Z (offset 2x1 rows), T (3x1 with center foot)\n- **Controls:** Left/Right arrows to move, Up arrow to rotate, Down arrow to drop\n- **Scoring:** 1 line = 50 pts, 2 lines = 100 pts, 3 lines = 200 pts, 4 lines = 500 pts\n- **Speed:** Increases every 1000 points\n- **Game over:** When a new piece cannot spawn (reaches top)\n- **High scores:** Prompt for initials, persist in localStorage, display leaderboard\n- **Start:** Game begins when user presses a Start button; option to play again after game over","status":"PLANNED","sort_order":"a0","labels":["epic"]},"created_at":"2026-07-12T12:38:00.672027Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
{"id":"xpoinittest-86923f","type":"CREATE","payload":{"title":"Project scaffolding — React app with 2D rendering","description":"## What\n\nSet up the React project with a suitable 2D rendering approach for the COLORBLOXX game.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] React app bootstrapped (Vite or similar)\n- [ ] 2D rendering strategy chosen and integrated (HTML5 Canvas, or a lightweight lib like PixiJS)\n- [ ] App runs in dev mode with hot reload\n- [ ] Basic project structure in place (components/, game/, etc.)","status":"PLANNED","parent_id":"xpoinittest-69a413","estimate":2,"sort_order":"a1","labels":["feature"]},"created_at":"2026-07-12T12:38:09.067389Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
{"id":"xpoinittest-dbf112","type":"CREATE","payload":{"title":"Game board \u0026 grid rendering","description":"## What\n\nRender a 10x20 COLORBLOXX playfield and display it centered on screen.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] 10-column x 20-row grid rendered on canvas/component\n- [ ] Each cell is visually distinct (grid lines or borders)\n- [ ] Board is centered and responsively sized\n- [ ] Empty board displays correctly on load","status":"BACKLOG","parent_id":"xpoinittest-69a413","estimate":2,"sort_order":"a0","labels":["feature"]},"created_at":"2026-07-12T12:38:12.033245Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
{"id":"xpoinittest-5432c1","type":"CREATE","payload":{"title":"Tetromino shapes \u0026 spawning","description":"## What\n\nDefine the four tetromino shapes with their rotation states and implement random spawning at the top of the board.\n\n## Pieces\n\n- **Square (O):** 2x2 block\n- **Bar (I):** 4x1 horizontal bar\n- **Z:** Two 2x1 rows offset by one column\n- **T:** 3x1 top row with 1 block centered below\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] All four shapes defined with distinct colors\n- [ ] Each shape has all rotation states (0°, 90°, 180°, 270°)\n- [ ] Random piece selection on spawn\n- [ ] Piece spawns at top-center of the board\n- [ ] Spawned piece renders on the board","status":"BACKLOG","parent_id":"xpoinittest-69a413","estimate":3,"sort_order":"a1","labels":["feature"]},"created_at":"2026-07-12T12:38:16.235263Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
{"id":"xpoinittest-d048e8","type":"CREATE","payload":{"title":"Movement \u0026 collision detection","description":"## What\n\nImplement left/right/down movement with boundary and piece collision detection.\n\n## Controls\n\n- **Left arrow:** Move piece one column left\n- **Right arrow:** Move piece one column right\n- **Down arrow:** Hard drop (instant fall to lowest valid position)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Left/right movement responds to arrow keys\n- [ ] Pieces cannot move through walls or other locked pieces\n- [ ] Down arrow instantly drops the piece to the lowest valid row\n- [ ] Automatic downward movement on a timer (gravity)","status":"BACKLOG","parent_id":"xpoinittest-69a413","estimate":3,"sort_order":"a2","labels":["feature"]},"created_at":"2026-07-12T12:38:19.510828Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
{"id":"xpoinittest-0450f4","type":"CREATE","payload":{"title":"Rotation","description":"## What\n\nImplement piece rotation using the Up arrow key with wall-kick logic to handle rotations near boundaries.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Up arrow rotates piece 90° clockwise\n- [ ] Rotation is blocked if the resulting position collides with walls or locked pieces\n- [ ] Basic wall kick: if rotation collides, try shifting piece left/right to make it fit\n- [ ] Square piece does not visually change on rotation (all states identical)","status":"BACKLOG","parent_id":"xpoinittest-69a413","estimate":2,"sort_order":"a3","labels":["feature"]},"created_at":"2026-07-12T12:38:23.298118Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
{"id":"xpoinittest-ad5f64","type":"CREATE","payload":{"title":"Piece locking \u0026 line clearing","description":"## What\n\nLock a piece into the board when it lands, detect and clear completed rows, and shift rows down.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Piece locks into the grid when it can no longer move down\n- [ ] Full rows (all 10 cells filled) are detected\n- [ ] Completed rows are removed and rows above shift down\n- [ ] Multiple simultaneous line clears work correctly (1–4 lines)\n- [ ] A new piece spawns after locking","status":"BACKLOG","parent_id":"xpoinittest-69a413","estimate":3,"sort_order":"a4","labels":["feature"]},"created_at":"2026-07-12T12:38:27.085882Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
{"id":"xpoinittest-6574d4","type":"CREATE","payload":{"title":"Scoring \u0026 speed progression","description":"## What\n\nImplement the point system and progressive speed increase.\n\n## Scoring Table\n\n| Lines Cleared | Points |\n|---------------|--------|\n| 1             | 50     |\n| 2             | 100    |\n| 3             | 200    |\n| 4             | 500    |\n\n## Speed\n\n- Gravity speed increases every 1000 points\n- Base interval decreases progressively (e.g., 800ms → 700ms → 600ms → ...)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Score displays on screen and updates on line clears\n- [ ] Correct point values awarded per simultaneous line clear\n- [ ] Drop speed increases every 1000 points\n- [ ] Current level/speed indicator visible to the player","status":"BACKLOG","parent_id":"xpoinittest-69a413","estimate":2,"sort_order":"a5","labels":["feature"]},"created_at":"2026-07-12T12:38:30.970865Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
{"id":"xpoinittest-094c11","type":"CREATE","payload":{"title":"Game over \u0026 restart flow","description":"## What\n\nDetect game-over condition and implement the end-of-game flow.\n\n## Flow\n\n1. New piece spawns and immediately collides → game over\n2. Show game-over overlay\n3. Prompt player to enter 3-letter initials\n4. Display high score table\n5. Offer \"Play Again\" button\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Game over triggers when a new piece cannot be placed\n- [ ] Game-over overlay/modal appears\n- [ ] Player can enter initials (max 3 characters)\n- [ ] \"Play Again\" resets the board, score, and speed\n- [ ] Start button on initial load begins the game","status":"BACKLOG","parent_id":"xpoinittest-69a413","estimate":3,"sort_order":"a6","labels":["feature"]},"created_at":"2026-07-12T12:38:35.244375Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
{"id":"xpoinittest-f42f98","type":"CREATE","payload":{"title":"High scores with localStorage","description":"## What\n\nPersist high scores in localStorage and display a leaderboard.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Scores saved to localStorage with initials, score, and date\n- [ ] Top 10 scores displayed in a leaderboard table\n- [ ] Leaderboard shown after game over and accessible from main screen\n- [ ] Scores persist across page reloads\n- [ ] New high score is highlighted in the list","status":"BACKLOG","parent_id":"xpoinittest-69a413","estimate":2,"sort_order":"a7","labels":["feature"]},"created_at":"2026-07-12T12:38:37.937393Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
