{"id":"xpoinittest-86923f","type":"COMMENT","payload":{"id":"cmt-402f2e49-569f-456a-9cbd-fbb51e54aa7b","text":"## Summary\n\nScaffolded a React + TypeScript app using Vite (via `bunx create-vite`). Cleaned all demo boilerplate and set up the project structure:\n\n- `src/components/` — `GameCanvas.tsx` renders an HTML5 Canvas with the 10x20 grid\n- `src/game/` — `constants.ts` defines grid dimensions (COLS, ROWS, CELL_SIZE)\n- `src/hooks/` — empty, ready for game loop and keyboard hooks\n\n## Rationale\n\n- **HTML5 Canvas over a game framework** — COLORBLOXX only needs `fillRect`/`strokeRect`; no physics, sprites, or scene graph required. Keeps the bundle minimal.\n- **bun** — per user preference for package management and dev tooling.\n- **Dark theme baseline** — game-appropriate dark background from the start.\n\n## Decisions made\n\n- Grid cell size set to 30px (board renders at 300x600px) — large enough to be playable without scrolling on most screens.\n- Stripped the Vite favicon SVG reference (can add a custom one later).\n\n## Status\n\nTypeScript compiles clean (`tsc --noEmit` passes), dev server starts and serves the canvas grid. Ready for review."},"created_at":"2026-07-12T12:45:48.627403Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
