{"id":"xpoinittest-5432c1","type":"COMMENT","payload":{"id":"cmt-dd7b835a-0e07-4208-b654-b25fd622b54e","text":"## Summary\n\n- Created `src/game/pieces.ts` — defines all 4 tetrominoes (O, I, Z, T) with explicit rotation matrices and distinct colors\n- Created `src/game/player.ts` — `Player` type, `spawnPlayer()` (random piece at top-center), `getShape()` helper\n- Updated `src/components/GameCanvas.tsx` — added `drawPlayer()` to overlay active piece on the board\n- Updated `src/App.tsx` — holds player state, spawns on mount\n\n## Rationale\n\nExplicit rotation matrices avoid programmatic rotation bugs (especially with the non-square I-piece). Player position uses top-left-of-matrix convention for simple cell offset math.\n\n## Status\n\nTypeScript compiles clean. Random piece renders at top-center with beveled tiles on each page load. Ready for review."},"created_at":"2026-07-12T12:55:45.826022Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
