{"id":"xpoinittest-5fcc95","type":"CREATE","payload":{"dependencies":[{"kind":"depends_on","source_id":"xpoinittest-5fcc95","target_id":"xpoinittest-d048e8"}],"description":"## What\n\nShow a preview of the next piece that will spawn, displayed in a small panel beside the game board.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Next piece is determined when current piece spawns\n- [ ] Preview panel rendered next to the board showing the upcoming piece\n- [ ] Preview updates each time a new piece spawns\n- [ ] Preview uses the same beveled cell rendering as the board","estimate":2,"labels":["feature"],"parent_id":"xpoinittest-69a413","sort_order":"a8","status":"BACKLOG","title":"Next piece preview"},"created_at":"2026-07-12T13:02:04.89588Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
{"id":"xpoinittest-bf1a50","type":"CREATE","payload":{"dependencies":[{"kind":"depends_on","source_id":"xpoinittest-bf1a50","target_id":"xpoinittest-d048e8"}],"description":"## What\n\nAdd a short lock delay when a piece lands, giving the player a brief window to slide or rotate the piece before it locks into the board.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] When a piece can no longer move down, a lock delay timer starts (~500ms)\n- [ ] During the delay, the player can still move left/right or rotate\n- [ ] If a successful move resets the piece to a non-landed state, the delay cancels\n- [ ] If the delay expires without movement, the piece locks normally\n- [ ] Hard drop bypasses the lock delay (locks immediately)","estimate":2,"labels":["feature"],"parent_id":"xpoinittest-69a413","sort_order":"a9","status":"BACKLOG","title":"Lock delay polish"},"created_at":"2026-07-12T13:02:09.045017Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
{"id":"xpoinittest-5220ac","type":"CREATE","payload":{"dependencies":[{"kind":"depends_on","source_id":"xpoinittest-5220ac","target_id":"xpoinittest-d048e8"}],"description":"## What\n\nShow a start screen on initial load instead of immediately starting the game. The game only begins when the player clicks a prominent START GAME button.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] On load, the board is empty and no pieces fall\n- [ ] A large, prominent START GAME button is displayed\n- [ ] Clicking the button starts the game (first piece spawns, gravity begins)\n- [ ] Keyboard controls are inactive until the game starts\n- [ ] The start screen fits the retro aesthetic","estimate":2,"labels":["feature"],"parent_id":"xpoinittest-69a413","sort_order":"aA","status":"BACKLOG","title":"Start screen — require START GAME button to begin"},"created_at":"2026-07-12T13:02:13.376683Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
{"id":"xpoinittest-f5a6ca","type":"CREATE","payload":{"dependencies":[{"kind":"depends_on","source_id":"xpoinittest-f5a6ca","target_id":"xpoinittest-d048e8"}],"description":"## What\n\nShow a transparent preview of where the current piece would land if hard-dropped, rendered as a ghost/shadow on the board.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Ghost piece displayed at the lowest valid position directly below the active piece\n- [ ] Ghost uses the piece's color but with reduced opacity (~30%)\n- [ ] Ghost updates in real-time as the player moves or rotates\n- [ ] Ghost does not interfere with collision detection or game logic\n- [ ] Ghost is not shown if the piece is already at the landing position","estimate":2,"labels":["feature"],"parent_id":"xpoinittest-69a413","sort_order":"aB","status":"BACKLOG","title":"Drop shadow (ghost piece)"},"created_at":"2026-07-12T13:02:17.288508Z","created_by":"claude-code/2.1.207 \u003cagent@mcp\u003e","on_behalf_of":"Nicolas Bettenburg \u003cnicbet@gmail.com\u003e","source":"mcp"}
